- What ntp does is that it use udp(PORT 123) protocol to provide accurate time information
- name of ntp daemon is ntpd	

# to use ntpdate
$ sudo dnf install ntp
$ sudo dnf install ntpdate		# sets time and date via NTP
$ man ntpdate

# ro set manual ntp server
$ sudo ntpdate server ip
$ sudo ntpdate 1.pool.ntp.org

# Bydefault ntp server info is located at
# /etc/ntp.conf

# use ntpstat to see status
$ npstat

# NTP query programme
$ ntpq  

# An impotant command
# ntpq -pn
#
#
